abstract: Floyd Norris Off the Charts column observes that apparel prices, which fell in last 10 years and then stabilized, have begun to increase; points out labor costs in China, major exporter of apparel, are rising; charts show rise in Consumer Price Index for apparel.
snippet: Apparel prices, which fell in the last 10 years and then stabilized, have begun to increase.
lead_paragraph: Apparel prices, which fell in the last 10 years and then stabilized, have begun to increase.
